{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Zechariah

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lesson from the Past

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}In the eighth month in the second year of Darius, this message of the {\scaps Lord} came to the prophet Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The {\scaps Lord} was furious with your ancestors.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So tell the people this message of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts: \uc1\u8220*Return to me,\uc1\u8221* says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, \uc1\u8220*and I will return to you\uc1\u8221* says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}\uc1\u8220*Do not be like your ancestors to whom the former prophets cried, \uc1\u8216*The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says to turn now from your evil ways, and from your evil deeds\uc1\u8217*. They did not heed nor listen to me,\uc1\u8221* says the {\scaps Lord}.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8220*Your ancestors, where are they? And the prophets, do they live forever?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But did not my words and my statutes with which I charged my servants the prophets overtake your ancestors? And they repented and said, \uc1\u8216*Just as the {\scaps Lord} of hosts planned to do to us, according to our ways, and according to our deeds, so he has dealt with us.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord\uc1\u8217*s Jealous Love for Zion

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}In the twenty-fourth day of the eleventh month, which is the month Shebat, in the second year of Darius, this message of the {\scaps Lord} came to the prophet Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I saw in the night a man on a red horse, among the myrtle trees that were in the valley-bottom. Behind him there were horses, red, sorrel, and white.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then said I, \uc1\u8220*My Lord, what are these?\uc1\u8221* And the messenger who was talking with me said, \uc1\u8220*I will show you what they are.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And the man who was standing among the myrtle trees answered, \uc1\u8220*They are those whom the {\scaps Lord} has sent to patrol the earth.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And the riders answered the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} who was standing among the myrtle trees, \uc1\u8220*We have gone up and down through the world and behold, all the earth is still and at peace.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said, \uc1\u8220*{\scaps Lord} of hosts, how long will you have no pity for Jerusalem and the cities of Judah with which you have been angry for seventy years?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And the {\scaps Lord} answered the messenger who was talking with me with kind and comforting words.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So the messenger who was talking with me said to me, \uc1\u8220*Proclaim now that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts says: I am deeply concerned for Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But I am deeply angry with the arrogant, complacent nations. I was only a little angry with Israel but they made the suffering worse.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore, says the {\scaps Lord}, I am turning to show mercy to Jerusalem. My temple will be rebuilt in it, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, and a measuring line will be stretched over Jerusalem.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Proclaim again: Thus says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts: My cities will again overflow with prosperity and the {\scaps Lord} will again comfort Zion and choose Jerusalem.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Destruction of the Heathen Powers

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Now I looked up and saw four horns.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I said to the messenger who was talking with me, \uc1\u8220*What are these?\uc1\u8221* He answered, \uc1\u8220*These are the horns which scattered Judah, Israel and Jerusalem.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then the {\scaps Lord} showed me four smiths.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}I said, \uc1\u8220*What are these coming to do?\uc1\u8221* He answered, \uc1\u8220*The horns scattered Judah, so that no one dared lift their head. But the smiths have come to terrify them, to crush the horns of the nations which lifted up their horn against the land of Judah to scatter its people.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Promise that Jerusalem Will be Gloriously Restored

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Then I looked up and saw a man with a measuring line in his hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}I said, \uc1\u8220*Where are you going?\uc1\u8221* He replied, \uc1\u8220*To measure Jerusalem, to see what is its breadth and length.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then the messenger who talked with me stepped forward, and another messenger went out to meet him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and said to him, \uc1\u8220*Run and tell to that young man that Jerusalem will be inhabited like a village without walls, because so many people and cattle will live there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For I, says the {\scaps Lord}, will be a wall of fire around her, and I will be the glory in the midst of her.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Up! Away! Flee from the land of the north, says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
For I have spread you abroad as the four winds of the heavens, says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Up, escape to Zion, you who live in Babylon.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}This is what the {\scaps Lord} of hosts says to the nations which plundered you:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Whoever touches you touches the apple of my eye.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}I will raise my hand against them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
They will be plunder for their own slaves; and you will know that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has sent me.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*Sing and rejoice, daughter of Zion! I am coming,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will live among you, says the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Many nations will join themselves to the {\scaps Lord} in that day,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and will be his people, and he will live among you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
You will know that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has sent me to you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The {\scaps Lord} will inherit Judah as his portion in the holy land.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
He will again choose Jerusalem.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Be silent, everyone, in the presence of the {\scaps Lord},
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
because he is coming from his holy dwelling.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Purification of the Priesthood and Nation

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Then he showed me Joshua, the high priest, standing before the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} and the Adversary standing at his right hand to accuse him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said to the Adversary, \uc1\u8220*May the {\scaps Lord} rebuke you, Adversary! The {\scaps Lord}, who has chosen Jerusalem, rebuke you! Is not this man a brand plucked out of the fire?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Now Joshua was clothed with filthy garments and was standing before the messenger.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The messenger said to those who stood before him, \uc1\u8220*Take off his filthy garments.\uc1\u8221* Then to Joshua he said, \uc1\u8220*I have taken your guilt from you and I will clothe you in priestly robes.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And he ordered: \uc1\u8220*Set a clean turban upon his head.\uc1\u8221* So they set a clean turban on his head, and clothed him with garments. The messenger of the {\scaps Lord} was standing by.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} testified to Joshua:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says: \uc1\u8220*If you walk in my ways, and if you will keep my instructions, then you will rule my house and keep my courts and I will give you a place of access among these that stand by.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Hear now, Joshua the high priest, you and your associates who sit before me; for they are men who are a sign; for I am going to bring forth my servant the Branch.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}On the stone that I have set before Joshua, on one stone, are seven facets. I will engrave it,\uc1\u8221* says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, \uc1\u8220*and I will remove the guilt of that land in one day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}On that day,\uc1\u8221* says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, \uc1\u8220*you will each invite your neighbor under the vine and under the fig tree.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Supporters of the Temple Service

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Then the messenger who talked with me came again and woke me, as someone who is woken from sleep.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He said to me, \uc1\u8220*What do you see?\uc1\u8221* I said, \uc1\u8220*I see a candlestick, all of gold, with a bowl on its top, and seven lamps on it. There are seven pipes to each of the lamps, which are on its top,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and two olive trees next to it, one on the right side of the bowl, and the other on its left side.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I said to the messenger who talked with me, \uc1\u8220*What are these, my lord?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then the messenger who talked with me answered, \uc1\u8220*Don\uc1\u8217*t you know what these are?\uc1\u8221* And I said. \uc1\u8220*No, my lord.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}He said to me, \uc1\u8220*This is the message of the {\scaps Lord} regarding Zerubbabel: Not by might, nor by power, but by my spirit, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}will I make the great mountain before Zerubbabel a plain. He will bring forth the top stones with shoutings of, \uc1\u8216*Grace, grace, to it.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Moreover this message of the {\scaps Lord} came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundation of this house. His hands will also finish it. Then you will know that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has sent me to you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For who has despised the day of small things? They will rejoice, and will see the plumb line in the hand of Zerubbabel. (The seven lamps are the eyes of the {\scaps Lord} that search all around the world.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Again I asked, \uc1\u8220*What are these two olive trees on the right side of the candlestick and on its left side?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Again, \uc1\u8220*What are these two branches of the olive trees, which are pouring out the golden oil through the two golden pipes?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}He answered me, \uc1\u8220*Don\uc1\u8217*t you now what these are?\uc1\u8221* And I said, \uc1\u8220*No, my lord.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Then he explained, \uc1\u8220*They are the two anointed ones who attend the Lord of all the earth.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Flying Scroll

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}Then again I looked up and saw a flying scroll.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}He said to me, \uc1\u8220*What do you see?\uc1\u8221* I answered, \uc1\u8220*I see a flying scroll; twenty cubits long, ten cubits wide.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then he said to me, \uc1\u8220*This is the curse that goes over the whole land. Every thief will be banished according to the writing on one side and everyone who lies under oath shall be banished according to the writing on the other side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}I have sent it out, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, and it will enter into the house of the thief, and into the house of anyone who swears falsely by my name. It will remain in the midst of his house and will consume it with its timber and its stones.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Woman in an Ephah

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then the messenger who talked with me came forward, and said to me, \uc1\u8220*Look up and see what is now coming.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}I said. \uc1\u8220*What is it?\uc1\u8221* He said, \uc1\u8220*It is a measuring basket, full of the guilt of the land.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}A round leaden cover was lifted up, and there was a woman sitting in the middle of the basket.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}He said, \uc1\u8220*This is Wickedness.\uc1\u8221* He thrust her down into the midst of the basket and he pushed the round leaden cover back on its mouth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then I looked up and saw two women, and the wind was in their wings. They had wings like the wings of a stork and they lifted up the basket between them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Then I said to the messenger who talked with me, \uc1\u8220*Where are they taking the basket?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}He said to me, \uc1\u8220*To build her a house in the land of Shinar. When it is prepared, they will rest the basket there.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The War-Chariots of the Lord

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Again I looked up, and saw four chariots come from between two mountains. The mountains were mountains of bronze.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The first chariot had red horses. The second chariot had black horses,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}the third chariot white horses, and the fourth chariot dappled horses.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Then I said to the messenger who talked with me, \uc1\u8220*What are these, my lord?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The messenger answered me, \uc1\u8220*These are the four winds of heaven going out after standing before the {\scaps Lord} of all the earth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The black horses are going toward the north country and the white toward the west and the dappled toward the south country.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The strong horses came out, and were impatient to patrol the earth. So he said, \uc1\u8220*Go, patrol the earth,\uc1\u8221* and they did so.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Then he cried out to me, \uc1\u8220*The horses that went to the north country will quiet my spirit in the north country.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Preparations for the Crowning of Zerubbabel

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Now this message of the {\scaps Lord} came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Take the gifts from the exiles Heldai, Tobijah and Jedaiah who have come from Babylon and go at once to Josiah the son of Zephaniah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Take their silver and gold and make a crown and set it on the head of the high priest, Joshua son of Jehozadak.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Tell him: \uc1\u8220*Thus says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts: Behold, the man whose name is the Branch. He will branch out from his place and rebuild the temple of the {\scaps Lord}.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}He will rebuild the temple and will sit and rule upon his throne, receiving the honor due to a king. A priest will stand by his throne and they will work together in peace and harmony.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}The crown will be a memorial in the temple of the {\scaps Lord} for Heldai and Tobijah and Jedaiah, and Josiah the son of Zephaniah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}People from far away will come and build in the temple of the {\scaps Lord} and you will know that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts has sent me to you. This will happen if you diligently obey the voice of the {\scaps Lord} your God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Lord\uc1\u8217*s Real Demands

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}In the fourth year of the reign of King Darius, on the fourth day of Chislev, the ninth month, the message of the {\scaps Lord} came to Zechariah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The city of Bethel had sent Sharezer and Regem-melech and their men, to entreat the favor of the {\scaps Lord},{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and to ask the priests of the house of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, and the prophets \uc1\u8220*Should I continue to mourn in the fifth month, separating myself, as I have done for many years?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Then this message of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Tell all the people of the land and the priests, \uc1\u8220*When you fasted and mourned in the fifth and in the seventh month, for these seventy years, did you really fast for me?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}When you eat and when you drink, do you not eat for yourselves, and drink for yourselves?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Wasn\uc1\u8217*t it this which the {\scaps Lord} proclaimed by the earlier prophets, when Jerusalem was inhabited and prosperous, and her towns surrounding her and the Negreb and the Shephelah were inhabited?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}The {\scaps Lord} gave this message to Zechariah:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says, execute true judgments. Show kindness and mercy to each other.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Do not oppress the widow or the orphan, the resident foreigner or the poor. Let none of you devise evil against another in your hearts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But they refused to listen, and turned a stubborn shoulder, and stopped their ears so they wouldn\uc1\u8217*t hear.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}They made their hearts as hard as stone so they wouldn\uc1\u8217*t accept the teaching and the words that the {\scaps Lord} of hosts had sent by his spirit through the earlier prophets. Great was the anger of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}I called and they would not hear, so they call and I do not hear, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}I scattered them by a whirlwind out among nations unknown to them. The land was left desolate behind them, with no one crossing or returning, for they made the pleasant land a desolation.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Promises that the Scattered Exiles Will Return and the Lord\uc1\u8217*s Rule be Widely Acknowledged

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}Now this message of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts came to me:
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I passionately care for Zion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I am fiercely protective of her.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}The {\scaps Lord} says, I have returned to Zion,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and will dwell in the midst of Jerusalem
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and Jerusalem will be called, \uc1\u8216*The City of Truth\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the mountain of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts, \uc1\u8216*The Holy Mountain.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Old men and old women will sit again in the squares of Jerusalem,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
each leaning on a staff because of old age.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And the streets of the city will be full of boys,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and of girls playing in its squares.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
Just because it seems impossible to the remnant of this people in these days,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
is it also impossible for me? says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will rescue my people
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
from the land of the east and the land of the west.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}I will bring them and they will live in Jerusalem,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and they will be my people,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I will be their God,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in truth and righteousness.
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The {\scaps Lord} of hosts says: Let your hands be strong, you who hear in these days the words of the prophets spoken when the foundations for the house of the {\scaps Lord} of hosts were laid.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For before those days there were no wages for people or animals. No one could go out or return safe from enemies, because I set each against their neighbor.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But now I will treat the remnant of the people differently from former days, says the {\scaps Lord} of hosts.
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Peace will be sown.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
The vine will bear its fruit and the ground will yield its produce,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the skies will give their dew.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
I will give the remnant of this people all these things.
